{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Centre Elementary School","telephone":"(256) 927-3302","address":{"streetAddress":"725 E Main St","addressLocality":"Centre","addressCountry":"US","addressRegion":"AL","postalCode":"35960"},"review":[{"author":"Adam S.","datePublished":"2016-10-26","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":1},"description":"This &quot;school&quot; and I use that term loosely, has a horrible staff. Their principal Wes Neyman is rude, unprofessional and down right small minded. I have a special needs child with Autism. We have tried working with the staff of this establishment on many occasions regarding the educational plans for our child. On numerous occasions blame has been made and accusations made that we not only physically abuse our child (DFACS came to our house and we passed with flying colors and they also noted there were zero identifying marks that would raise suspicion of physical abuse) these people actually tried to use DFACS against us just to be spiteful when we did not agree with the methods being used. The straw that broke the camels back came when the principal told my wife that our childs behavior was &quot;not normal&quot;. He gets a golden star for being observant. Most Autistic children do not fit the moniker of &quot;normal&quot; but that does not in any way make them less special or relevant. Avoid this school if for any other reason that there is zero established standard of professionalism and courtesy. These people will treat you horribly and I suggest just steering clear altogether.

Thanks, 
A frustrated parent."}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":1,"reviewCount":1}}

{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Lost Bay Helicopters","image":"https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Hs-fvPvPt_XHHyHEMCOJuQ/l.jpg","telephone":"(772) 834-4497","address":{"streetAddress":"3190 Airport Dr","addressLocality":"Gulf Shores","addressCountry":"US","addressRegion":"AL","postalCode":"36542"},"review":[{"author":"Angela R.","datePublished":"2022-06-18","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"My first helicopter ride today and it was well worth it. Great flight and great experience. Definitely would recommend Lost Bay Helicopters!"},{"author":"Nikita S.","datePublished":"2022-04-07","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"Had amazing time with pilot Mike and much appreciated meeting with Rachel, business owner, highly recommend checking them out if you are in town for a weekend, totally worth the price!"},{"author":"Justin E.","datePublished":"2020-08-19","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"Most of these guys are ex military and I always try to support vets and vet businesses and this business is the exact reason why. They run it the way a business should be with great precision and outstanding customer service with Rachael keeping everything and everyone in order.
Great experience and I highly recommend them!"},{"author":"Shelby G.","datePublished":"2021-09-24","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":3},"description":"My daughters been dying to fly so when I seen their ad pop up on fb while we were on vacation I jumped on it. I wish I hadn&apos;t the pilot didn&apos;t say a word to us when we got in which made it kind of awkward in my opinion. My 7 year old daughter sat in the front with him she was so excited it was her first time flying and it was a surprise birthday present for her. I&apos;ve went on a helicopter ride down here a few years ago and it was great the guy talked to us the whole time asked where we were staying so we could fly by and wave I&apos;ll be taking her there if we ever want to go again. When we got done she was like why didn&apos;t he say hi how are you or bye have a nice day i hope you enjoyed it when we got out that was awkward. i asked which way we were going and he told me left down the beach and across state park and thats the only thing he ever said. The lady that walks you to the helicopter was super nice and friendly.  Luckily my daughter still enjoyed it and it wasn&apos;t a total bust for her."},{"author":"Katherine L.","datePublished":"2018-05-22","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"I can&apos;t believe that I&apos;m the first to review.  For about a hundie, the two of you can have the most incredible tourist thing.  The pilot (is adorable) is knowledgeable, gives competent instructions without terrifying you, then lifts you off of the tarmac before you can start to panic about being hoisted 500 feet off terra firma in a glass bubble glued to a beer can.  The panic lasts only a couple seconds, then ... OMG.  Just.  Wow.  It&apos;s a short trip around the Gulf Shores city, beach and state park.  The pilot loves his little neck of the woods and ADORES his machine.  He is happy to share info and explain intricacies of his aircraft.  And ...  drumroll .... you get to wear those cool headphones with microphones attached.  Do this tourist thing.  Its fun to go hang around the airport, too.  

AFTERTHOUGHT:  It is not, in fact, a beer can.  It&apos;s an amazing, well-kept, well-loved flying machine.  I did not mean to make it sound otherwise."}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":4.5,"reviewCount":5}}

{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Calera Middle School","image":"https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/wZFFBhT1_D0WfwM4fhxOGg/l.jpg","telephone":"(205) 682-6100","address":{"streetAddress":"9178 Hwy 22","addressLocality":"Montevallo","addressCountry":"US","addressRegion":"AL","postalCode":"35115"},"review":[{"author":"Gabe P.","datePublished":"2019-12-18","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"CMS is a beautiful campus!  The grounds are well kept and the inside of the school is really tidy.  

Anytime I attend an event here, I always enjoy the environment.  The office staff as well as the  educators are all really professional!

I attended the Christmas concert and it was amazing. The show was well thought out and loaded with talented kids!  Great event!"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":5,"reviewCount":1}}

{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"La Costa Meadows Elementary School","image":"https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/1t2t0CkmtwkeN7-H-5Mddg/l.jpg","telephone":"(760) 290-2121","address":{"streetAddress":"6889 El Fuerte St","addressLocality":"Carlsbad","addressCountry":"US","addressRegion":"CA","postalCode":"92009"},"review":[{"author":"Christine S.","datePublished":"2016-10-05","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":4},"description":"Well organized school that is currently rated in the top two elementary schools in Carlsbad using educational scores on the great schools site.  I love that the school culture encourages friendship, collaboration, good citizenship via &quot;The Dolphin Way&quot;. It&apos;s a set of values that is based on Franklin Covey&apos;s Seven Habits of Highly Effective People that is adapted for kids.

The current challenges at the school are that it has outgrown it&apos;s original buildings and facilities so the plans to completely rebuild the school are set to begin in the spring of 2017. It will make for a temporary hassle, but much like the rebuild of San Marcos High School, it will be a major improvement.

I love the teachers, administrative staff-- everyone is very professional, caring and friendly.  A great environment all around for learning at all levels."},{"author":"Dylan L.","datePublished":"2017-10-04","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"This is the best school ever! It has so much events that we get to participate in and it really teaches you a lot and this coming from a kid so I would now best this will always be my favorite school thx to me klimas and mrs stephonson"},{"author":"Melanie Y.","datePublished":"2016-10-27","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"Outstanding educators. Our twin 5th graders have been in separate classes (our request) each year. All 10 teachers have been outstanding. If that is not enough, the leadership is top notch, especially Asst. Principal who has handled delicate issues with expertise, tact and, compassion. Strong school culture develops the whole child featuring Steven Covey&apos;s 7 Habits of Happy Kids into &quot;the dolphin way.&quot; The school was also a leader in implementing the common core curriculum."}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":4.5,"reviewCount":3}}

{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Over The Mountain Aviation","image":"https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/kjuS6qFpEpT5-hcckGONlQ/l.jpg","telephone":"(205) 670-6359","address":{"streetAddress":"265 Weathervane Rd","addressLocality":"Calera","addressCountry":"US","addressRegion":"AL","postalCode":"35040"},"review":[{"author":"Rick S.","datePublished":"2017-05-19","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":1},"description":"Went for an intro flight, plane was hot as hell doors/windows were not left open prior to flight nor was I told to dress comfortably, for an intro flight you think they would give you that info.  Poured sweat for the 10 minutes while on the ground.  

The headsets did not work, could not talk to the flight instructor to ask questions while in flight, yelling did not work so I just gave up even trying, huge disappointment !  The plane is about what you would expect for a training aircraft old and dirty but at least it worked, certainly does not get you excited about flying though.  No complaints about the flight instructor however he was great, it&apos;s not the instructor that ruined the experience it was everything else about it that did.

Highly recommend that you have working equipment (headsets) and warn customers about the heat especially on an intro flight in the summer, obviously some people on an intro flight don&apos;t fully know what to expect.  Ruined any interest I had in pursuing a ppl or flying from Over the Mountain again."},{"author":"Vic B.","datePublished":"2018-02-03","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"Great flight school with reasonable prices. Several planes to choose from and plenty of instructors. Taylor is a very smart CFI who will work with your schedule.  It&apos;s been such a pleasure flying here. Easy, low key, fun airport."},{"author":"Anthony F.","datePublished":"2016-01-13","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":1},"description":"Wanted to get my husband something special for his birthday.  Contacted over the mountain to set up discovery flight for my husband&apos;s birthday. Showed up at the time that I was given. The instructor stood us up, after he had confirmed our appointment  earlier in the day. I called and texted him and after  waiting 30 minutes finally left. He texted an hour later and stated he was just flying in. He suggested rescheduling and I did.What a mistake , again he disappointed us. Thank you so much for ruining my sweet husbands birthday.Terribly run business."}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":2.5,"reviewCount":3}}

{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Weinacker&apos;s Montessori School - Lake Forest","image":"https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/-ofFX3-sWNHq5A7NHQN78g/l.jpg","telephone":"(251) 259-5037","address":{"streetAddress":"28765 N Main St","addressLocality":"Daphne","addressCountry":"US","addressRegion":"AL","postalCode":"36526"},"review":[{"author":"Barcus P.","datePublished":"2022-04-22","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"I had 2 kids there from 2 years old to kindergarten at this location in the past and they loved it there. 

My kids thrived and were constantly learning new things. 

I wouldn&apos;t hesitate to recommend them to anyone."},{"author":"Leslie K.","datePublished":"2022-07-18","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"I have 2 kids attending since they were 3 months old, the eldest is now 4 and youngest is 16 months and I NEVER have to worry about the care and education they are receiving.  The teachers are compassionate and it&apos;s very clear they love what they do, as evident in how much both of my children love going to school.  I highly recommend Weinacker&apos;s Lake Forest if you are looking for a place to nurture your little ones."},{"author":"Katie L.","datePublished":"2018-09-26","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"This is an awesome school! Great atmosphere, great teachers and good location off of 98. My daughter loves it here!"},{"author":"Lori H.","datePublished":"2017-12-05","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"My older child went through the entire program at Weinackers. I could not be happier with the education he received. He is currently testing 6 grades above level, which I largely credit to his Montessori education.  My younger son started in the toddler room with Ms. Emily. She is a very loving and caring teacher and it is obvious that she personally invests in all of the children in her care. Since moving up to the pre-school he has continued to grow."}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":5,"reviewCount":4}}

{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Daphne Elementary School","image":"https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/MnJNWge6SiqQegtKCM3qlg/l.jpg","telephone":"(251) 626-2424","address":{"streetAddress":"2307 Main St","addressLocality":"Daphne","addressCountry":"US","addressRegion":"AL","postalCode":"36526"},"review":[{"author":"Tony M.","datePublished":"2016-10-26","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"Moving to LA (Lower Alabama) from out of state has been a difficult transition, but Daphne Elementary School (DES) has made our transition effortless. My children are now academically challenged and they couldn&apos;t be happier. They love the curriculum and everything that DES has to offer.

Mr. Bellmyer and Mrs. Scharwath are great teachers and I&apos;m glad we are lucky enough to have them as role models for our munchkins. Class sizes are small, the new leader program is amazing, and when they say they truly understand that &quot;one size does not fit all&quot;, they mean it! They even accommodated the school lunch menu to include vegetarian options for our child. My son loves using his iPad and my daughter has become very efficient at using her Chromebook. The only disappointment was that they do not offer Rosetta-Stone or dual language learning. Maybe this can be achieved in the near future. 

Principal Ellis is doing an amazing job and DES truly looks out for their students! It doesn&apos;t go unnoticed, keep up the great work!!"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":5,"reviewCount":1}}

