{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"The Studio - Fairfield","image":"https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/SWmePH5ay3RWs7rY4DHJjg/l.jpg","telephone":"(203) 814-6873","address":{"streetAddress":"43 Ruane St","addressLocality":"Fairfield","addressCountry":"US","addressRegion":"CT","postalCode":"06824"},"review":[{"author":"Fran S.","datePublished":"2022-07-27","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"Looking for a place to find your creativity? Check out The Studio - Fairfield. Truly amazing classes in wheel pottery, free-hand pottery, painting, and sculpture. The teachers are so caring and helpful. The Studio has the loveliest people who take classes and become members there. Everyone there is so encouraging and supportive. If you need a creative outlet (and who doesn&apos;t?) this is a wonderful place to experience. For me, it has become my version of therapy! #artheals"},{"author":"Murtuza H.","datePublished":"2019-09-25","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"Amazing classes!! They have adult and child classes which are amazing and then a variety of classes from painting, pottery, and sculpture.  Honestly, it doesn&apos;t get much better than that.  With that much variety, even I&apos;m able to call myself an artist.  Thanks so much for a great time :)"},{"author":"Gay G.","datePublished":"2019-09-09","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"I am so happy this place exists! I&apos;ve been taking adult drawing classes and will continue to do so. Perfect place for flexing rusty creative muscles and scratching an &apos;inner artist&apos; itch."},{"author":"Lindsey S.","datePublished":"2013-11-15","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":4},"description":"I attended the Adult Paint Night for a fun girls night out. It was a blast! When we got there everything was all set up; easels, paint, brushes, etc. and we just had to pick our seats. They provide smocks to wear and have lockers and cubbies to put your stuff in so you didn&apos;t have to worry about your coat or purse getting covered in paint.  Be brought a bunch of snacks and some wine and they provided the cups. 

It took a little while to finally get started but once we did the instructor gave us directions on what colors to mix, how to start with the background and then moved onto the foreground. My only complaint is that there wasn&apos;t a lot of direction after that. I am somewhat of a perfectionist and like structure so it&apos;s helpful for me to have directions on exactly what parts to work on and how to, but there wasn&apos;t a lot of it. 

Overall I would definitely recommend coming here. I used a livingsocial voucher and it was totally worth it! Can&apos;t wait to go back to also try the pottery class!"},{"author":"Hannah O.","datePublished":"2014-02-17","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"I come here all the time and it is so fun! I have tried pottery, painting, and silk screening t-shirts. The prices are great and Priscilla and Christine are very helpful and pretty laid back. I made some amazing hand and foot print ceramic ornaments of my 4 month old and they came out beautifully. They offer camps, memberships, and byob adult nights just to name a few. Definitely a place to come express yourself and be creative!"},{"author":"Shadin D.","datePublished":"2014-01-24","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"I tried the pottery class, and I had such a great time! The price includes 3 visits, and the final project is worth it! Christine helps with the pottery, and she is very knowledgable! My friends did the painting class and they loved it. I can&apos;t wait to go back and try it!"},{"author":"Karl S.","datePublished":"2014-05-06","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"Great place to take the kids to learn and  explore art from painting to pottery.  The teachers are wonderful and really know how to teach at any level and age group.  I am always amazed at the variety of creative projects they are doing."},{"author":"Dana D.","datePublished":"2014-07-18","reviewRating":{"ratingValue":5},"description":"Last night my my 60yr old father and myself went to the Thursday Night paint night and had a fantastic experience. Priscilla the art leader for the night was pleasant and helpful. My Dad is new to art and she helped guide him to find his inner artist! I am intermediate level and in the short 2.5hr class she definitely helped me grow my skills. The whole night was perfect! Fun, no pressure environment really made it a great place. My dad had a blast. We definitely will be back!!!"